Source: CoreWeave plans to cut the size of its IPO to ~$1.5B, offering 37.5M shares at $40 each, down from 49M shares at $47 to $55, a sign of market volatility (Bloomberg)

Google rolls out new Search, Maps, and Gemini features to help users plan vacations, including trip idea updates to AI Overviews and hotel price drop alerts (Aisha Malik/TechCrunch)
Client notice: Chinese server maker H3C warns of potential shortages of Nvidia H20 chips, the most advanced AI chips available in China under US export rules (Reuters)
